<p>discovered during this truce that there were even more casualties than had at first been reported 24.5.15</p>
<p>The Triumph was sunk by a torpedo today. She steamed about 2 miles and seemed to be making for Anzac but sunk about 1 &frac12; miles off Gaba Tepe. As she went down she fired a broadside. We hear that 60 of her crew were drowned 25.5.15.</p>
<p>We landed a trench mortar today. It is a Japanese invention and throws a projectile 28 lbs. weight a distance of about 1/3</p>
